item.title: Diana add a quote by Albert Einstein
item.description: "I am enough of an artist to draw freely upon my imagination. Imagination is more important than knowledge. Knowledge is limited. Imagination encircles the world." -- Albert Einstein

item.title: Diana add a quote by Bernard M. Baruch
item.description: "Be who you are and say what you feel, because those who mind don't matter, and those who matter don't mind." -- Bernard M. Baruch

item.title: Diana add a quote by Dr. Seuss
item.description: "Don't cry because it's over, smile because it happened." -- Dr. Seuss

item.title: Diana add a quote by John F. Kennedy
item.description: "If by a "Liberal" they mean someone who looks ahead and not behind, someone who welcomes new ideas without rigid reactions, someone who cares about the welfare of the people-their health, their housing, their schools, their jobs, their civil rights and their civil liberties-someone who believes we can break through the stalemate and suspicions that grip us in our policies abroad, if that is what they mean by a "Liberal", then I'm proud to say I'm a "Liberal." -- John F. Kennedy

item.title: Diana add a quote by John F. Kennedy
item.description: "To those whom much is given, much is expected." -- John F. Kennedy

item.title: Diana add a quote by Alice Roosevelt Longworth
item.description: "If you haven't got anything nice to say about anybody come sit next to me." -- Alice Roosevelt Longworth
